subSubSection.paragraph:
Differential diagnosis.
Recognized by the subserial or non-serial elytral punctures, the comparatively short maxillary palpi (palpus length/head width ca. 
0.64 mm
), and the comparatively large body size (length ca. 
2.17 mm
) (
Fig. 58
). The pronotal relief is M-shaped and very finely punctate, markedly contrasting with the rugose surrounding area. Like the habitus, the aedeagus stands apart from other members of the genus (
Fig. 76
).
